==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[nauseosus]]'', corresponding to ''[[nausea]]'' + ''[[-ous]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈnɔ:zɪəs/, /ˈnɔ:sɪəs/}} (''UK'')
*{{IPA|/ˈnɔ:ʃəs/}} (''US'')

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Causing [[nausea]]; [[sickening]] or [[disgusting]].

====Synonyms====
*[[nauseating]] - causing disgust rather than nausea

====See also====
*[[nauseated]] - afflicted with nausea

